      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Dataset copied from the CD obtained from Washington, DC 2005

The DC boundary coverage was created and the quadrants were identified from public records, including the ADC maps and heads-up digitized from the 1995 orthophotographs. The boundary and quadrant lines were intersected, and built. These resulting lines were used to generate the four polygons comprising the quadrants.   Attribute data was provided by public records. Planimetrics were created at a scale of 1:1,000. This means that a well defined feature falls within two feet of true position.

All DC GIS data is stored and exported in Maryland State Plane coordinates NAD 83 meters.</procdesc>
